// Event plane for mod_open_switch.
//
// FreeSWITCH events are bound by the module via `switch_event_bind`,
// classified into Tier 1/2/3, buffered briefly in per-tier in-memory
// rings, and delivered to active gRPC `SubscribeEvents` subscribers.
// `SubscribeEvents` is the sole event transport — there is no
// in-module Redis / Kafka / NATS producer. Subscribers persist to
// durable storage on their own side (Kafka, Redis Streams, S3, file,
// dashboard — operator's choice). See
// openspec/changes/core-module-v1/designs/transport-adr.md for the
// rationale.
//
// The `node_id` field on the envelope identifies the source FS
// instance; in multi-node deploys subscribers either filter by it or
// run one subscriber per node.
